# Clerk Billing

This app uses **Clerk Billing** (B2C) for all subscription and payment logic. Never integrate Stripe directly or build custom payment flows.

## Plans & Features

| Plan | Features |
|------|----------|
| `free_user` | `3_deck_limit` |
| `pro` | `unlimited_decks`, `ai_flashcard_generation` |

## Gating Access — Server Side (`has()`)

Use the `has()` helper from `auth()` to check plans or features in Server Components and Server Actions.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — check by plan
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { has } = await auth();
const isPro = has({ plan: "pro" });

// ✅ GOOD — check by feature
const canUseAI = has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" });
const hasUnlimitedDecks = has({ feature: "unlimited_decks" });
```

## Gating Access — Client Side (`<Show>`)

Use the `<Show>` component from `@clerk/nextjs` to conditionally render UI based on plan or feature.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — gate UI by feature
import { Show } from "@clerk/nextjs";

<Show
  when={{ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" }}
  fallback={<p>Upgrade to Pro to unlock AI flashcard generation.</p>}
>
  <AIGenerateButton />
</Show>

// ✅ GOOD — gate UI by plan
<Show
  when={{ plan: "pro" }}
  fallback={<UpgradeBanner />}
>
  <ProFeaturePanel />
</Show>
```

## Pricing Page

Use the `<PricingTable />` component on a dedicated pricing page. Never build a custom pricing table.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — app/pricing/page.tsx
import { PricingTable } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export default function PricingPage() {
  return <PricingTable />;
}
```

## Rules

- All plan slugs: `free_user`, `pro`
- All feature slugs: `3_deck_limit`, `unlimited_decks`, `ai_flashcard_generation`
- Use `has()` from `auth()` for server-side gating — never query a custom subscriptions table
- Use `<Show>` for client-side conditional rendering — never roll custom feature-flag logic
- Use `<PricingTable />` for pricing UI — never build a custom pricing table
- Clerk Billing manages Stripe under the hood — never call Stripe APIs directly
- Plans and features are configured in the Clerk Dashboard, not in code
